e/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0476260708920852e-17, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a total\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 304}, {\"ngram\": \"1,039 medals\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 320}, {\"ngram\": \"329 events\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 349}, {\"ngram\": \"32 different sports\", \"from\": 354, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"16 days\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 384}, {\"ngram\": \"an end\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 430}, {\"ngram\": \"thetorch\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was truly a Games to remember in Paris, withTeam GB narrowly eclipsing their medal haul from Tokyothree years ago, albeit with eight fewer golds as they finished in their lowest position in the final table since Athens 2004.\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 514, \"end\": 519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.616706516694945e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 530, \"end\": 532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7988081893479954, \"rank\": 0.25186498224737036, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 693, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.0650602367604765e-12, \"text\": \"Athens 2004\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Games\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"their medal haul\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"eight fewer golds\", \"from\": 608, \"to\": 625}, {\"ngram\": \"their lowest position\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"the final table\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 686}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New superstars were born and existing legends cemented their legacies across an unforgettable fortnight of thrills, spills and sporting drama of the highest quality.\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 872, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"New superstars\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"existing legends\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 752}, {\"ngram\": \"their legacies\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 776}, {\"ngram\": \"an unforgettable fortnight\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 810}, {\"ngram\": \"thrills\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 821}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting drama\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 848}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest quality\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 871}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Standard Sportreporters Matt Majendie and Malik Ouzia covered theParis Olympicsfrom start to finish and now review the best of the action as they saw it... Much like at London 2012, any time a home athlete was competing, the noise at the Paris venues was deafening.\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 1140, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malik\", \"score\": 0.9903836361514199, \"rank\": 0.009632944561846461, \"text\": \"Malik\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malik\"}, {\"begin\": 1044, \"end\": 1055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.685801479368546e-21, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1113, \"end\": 1118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.616706516694945e-29