restaurant, and renditions of La Marseillaise drifting down every street.\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1634, \"end\": 1639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.616706516694945e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1742, \"end\": 1757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3941369459247644e-44, \"text\": \"La Marseillaise\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two gold medals\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"a session\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1628}, {\"ngram\": \"that evening\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1652}, {\"ngram\": \"raucous celebrations\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1694}, {\"ngram\": \"every bar\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1707}, {\"ngram\": \"restaurant\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1722}, {\"ngram\": \"renditions\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"every street\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1784}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was, though, lucky enough to be there in person for his fourth and final gold medal and did not experience a better atmosphere all Games.MO Alex Yee looked to have settled for silver when his former flatmate Hayden Wilde, of New Zealand, sprung clear on the run leg of the individual triathlon and held a handy advantage going towards the race finish.\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1930, \"end\": 1938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 2005, \"end\": 2010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Wilde\", \"score\": 0.999999063062644, \"rank\": 7.901293122788117e-07, \"text\": \"Wilde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Wilde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Wilde\"}, {\"begin\": 2015, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.8933396627870828, \"rank\": 0.11255515183312169, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1836}, {\"ngram\": \"his fourth and final gold medal\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"a better atmosphere\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"all Games\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"the run leg\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2054}, {\"ngram\": \"the individual triathlon\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2082}, {\"ngram\": \"a handy advantage\", \"from\": 2092, \"to\": 2109}, {\"ngram\": \"the race finish\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2139}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But spurred on by a shout from two-time Olympic champion Alistair Brownlee, Yee decided to go for one final throw of the dice and suddenly started closing the gap quite dramatically, passing Wilde and then pulling well clear for the gold.MM I am not sure if it's personal preference or a widely-held view, but nothing quite beats a gold medal on the track.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2200, \"end\": 2217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alistair Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"dbpe