arned on this one); our hotel bar closing at 11pm; the US somehow finishing top, again, in the pool; Tommy Fleetwood's bogey on 17; being proven wrong when none of Timothee Chalamet, Kylian Mbappe or the chap from Lupin featured in the opening ceremony.MO The men's 1500m had long been billed as a straight head-to-head between Josh Kerr and Jakob Ingebrigtsen ever since Kerr got the better of the Norwegian at last summer's World Championships.\", \"from\": 4378, \"to\": 5063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4415, \"end\": 4420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.616706516694945e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4521, \"end\": 4533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Max Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}, {\"begin\": 4591, \"end\": 4597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.987956231309216, \"rank\": 0.011649390801718968, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4671, \"end\": 4673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6815017947171121, \"rank\": 0.46734246357534853, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4717, \"end\": 4732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tommy Fleetwood\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"db